<subSubSection id="17F52B6A97E533D65D8018130F9CC006" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="979E26B28BEC074704FCB09C5D643E6F" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="16F855BD1666505B07980179E645F95B" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">
Material of our new species most closely resembles specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="EB0B5081052F82254F35090BC011296A" authorityName="Harms" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="choristantha">
<emphasis id="6019E1475513D8F3E8C79ECE9178BC19" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta choristantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Harms from the Austral Islands, with which it shares a similarly structured inflorescence and totally free ovaries, but differs in leaf shape (narrowly obovate to spatulate in 
<taxonomicName id="9ECC4C2FCAA4545BC91D84633D358FBF" authorityName="F. Tronchet &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2011" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pastoralis">
<emphasis id="748AA5A748FC856B21C5F88CE39949B6" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta pastoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. widely elliptic to slightly obovate in 
<taxonomicName id="2272DA4B0AFF44800CB32653CD08C3AE" authorityName="Harms" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="choristantha">
<emphasis id="50B680EA6B3BA5D5806ACB323F0CC292" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta choristantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), number of carpels (5-11 vs. 5 or 6), and fruit size at maturity (7-9 
<normalizedToken id="846D7F519BA7B532042F320A7B035FAB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7-10 vs. 8-12 
<normalizedToken id="75914D3CA844CC6CC0BC6D0FBFEFB17D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10-15 mm). The leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="BAC2EAE174E5F7684C98E001D9D99745" authorityName="F. Tronchet &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2011" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pastoralis">
<emphasis id="23E795B99AC5AD4BC8FFCB6B2A93BA21" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta pastoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar in appearance to those of 
<taxonomicName id="9547FECE1A293803173EC81C79A6EFAF" authorityName="J. W. Moore" authorityYear="1963" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="raiateensis">
<emphasis id="35340549E8658D6997E6E5279D63FFF8" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta raiateensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
J.W. Moore, and to a lesser degree 
<taxonomicName id="268BB711BDBD908BABF86DA10690AE5F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis id="AA4143D7727DD5871E0832668A7DF92D" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
J.R. Forst. &amp; G. Forst., both from the Society Islands, but our new taxon differs from these entities, and indeed all other species in the Society Islands and on Tuamotu, by its totally free ovaries.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7352E42CBE6BAFAE975A32EF3FF8815" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">
Results from ongoing molecular phylogenetic work (
<bibRefCitation id="C526C90EF19165DB1AB70FF17578E6BC" author="Tronchet, F" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" pagination="657 - 670" publicationUrl="http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/aspt/sb/2005/00000030/00000003/art00016" refId="B10" refString="Tronchet, F, Plunkett, GM, Jeremie, J, Lowry II, PP, 2005a. Monophyly and major clades of Meryta (Araliaceae). Systematic Botany 30: 657 - 670, http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/aspt/sb/2005/00000030/00000003/art00016" title="Monophyly and major clades of Meryta (Araliaceae)." url="http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/aspt/sb/2005/00000030/00000003/art00016" volume="30" year="2005 a">Tronchet et al. 2005a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1D876AD187EA0A6B27791327CC2C3310" author="Tronchet, F" journalOrPublisher="Vienna, Austria" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" refId="B11" refString="Tronchet, F, Plunkett, GM, Jeremie, J, Lowry II, PP, 2005b. Phylogeny and biogeography of the Pacific genus Meryta (Araliaceae) based on ITS and ETS sequence data. In: Poster presented at the 17th International Botanical Congress. Vienna, Austria" title="Phylogeny and biogeography of the Pacific genus Meryta (Araliaceae) based on ITS and ETS sequence data." volumeTitle="Poster presented at the 17 th International Botanical Congress." year="2005 b">2005b</bibRefCitation>
, unpubl. data) suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="D4C83B3A4922D114ED0AC73050362323" authorityName="F. Tronchet &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2011" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pastoralis">
<emphasis id="9A2E9AE3BD95301EDC5EDD1C824D1206" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta pastoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of a small clade now understood to comprise four species, also including 
<taxonomicName id="81956A0F0368C133C49C31378A90EAB2" authorityName="Seem" authorityYear="1862" baseAuthorityName="Hook. f." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sinclairii">
<emphasis id="22DFE39989C1A6A8EEDF35FFBEE9EE02" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta sinclairii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from New Zealand, 
<taxonomicName id="5FC39DFD3F19B9387C07EA6FF4BF6A4C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis id="79A6903E52B5B7690832252340A48830" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A.C. Sm. from Fiji, and 
<taxonomicName id="4029FB790D20EC1C4604CFDE3327BA4D" authorityName="Harms" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="choristantha">
<emphasis id="62836118F2C7DB4FB1680B65126F7D72" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta choristantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which together correspond to 
<taxonomicName id="6A76F0C27290E12466D185C7DF25AEB6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1B07CC870D8CD069A671FDA2B6313DB5" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="D5EF33E8266932FCA259DB9E35CB30CA" genus="Choristomeryta" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="70F92FD0003E74603357473FB099CEF4" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Choristomeryta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Harms (
<bibRefCitation id="5E319FF2969C8B28B0C05D95405F8B89" author="Harms, H" journalOrPublisher="Notizblatt des botanischen Gartens und Muzeums zu Berlin-Dahlem" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" pagination="315 - 321" refId="B2" refString="Harms, H, 1938. Zur Kenntnis von Meryta sonchifolia Linden et Andre und einigen anderen Arten des Gattung. Notizblatt des botanischen Gartens und Muzeums zu Berlin-Dahlem 14: 315 - 321" title="Zur Kenntnis von Meryta sonchifolia Linden et Andre und einigen anderen Arten des Gattung." volume="14" year="1938">Harms 1938</bibRefCitation>
). Material here assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="D8D8DE12693996C83E6FA0BC4B820801" authorityName="F. Tronchet &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2011" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pastoralis">
<emphasis id="883D6923B4B0A02B7ADDD01C89B0F87B" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Meryta pastoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was referred to informally as 'M. 
<normalizedToken id="321C7A27D13B02E9767CC88494CD4F8F" originalValue="schaeferi’">schaeferi'</normalizedToken>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="312307EEEED7F1A93C8C16B3C2157669" author="Tronchet, F" journalOrPublisher="Vienna, Austria" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" refId="B11" refString="Tronchet, F, Plunkett, GM, Jeremie, J, Lowry II, PP, 2005b. Phylogeny and biogeography of the Pacific genus Meryta (Araliaceae) based on ITS and ETS sequence data. In: Poster presented at the 17th International Botanical Congress. Vienna, Austria" title="Phylogeny and biogeography of the Pacific genus Meryta (Araliaceae) based on ITS and ETS sequence data." volumeTitle="Poster presented at the 17 th International Botanical Congress." year="2005 b">Tronchet et al. (2005b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
